The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 May is 42,137 (4,877.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 May, there were 124 new confirmed cases (14.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 May, there were 111 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 12% (13 extra cases).
